"use strict";(self.webpackChunkgaming=self.webpackChunkgaming||[]).push([["300"],{5975(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"gud","metadata":{"permalink":"/gaming/blog/gud","source":"@site/blog/2026-05-15-gud.md","title":"Game Undefeatability Document (GUD)","description":"Ask yourself in your heart of hearts: \u201CWHY is there a near-ZERO chance that MY GAME will FLOP?\u201D","date":"2026-05-15T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"game design","permalink":"/gaming/blog/tags/game-design","description":"setting the game up to give the player the best possible feelings"},{"inline":false,"label":"marketing","permalink":"/gaming/blog/tags/marketing","description":"putting the game in front of many people"}],"readingTime":1.81,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Tiger.Whiskers","title":"UE5 DEV + 3D ART","socials":{"steam":"https://steamcommunity.com/id/TigerWhiskers","email":"mailto:ra9dev@gmail.com","attribution":"https://www.flaticon.com/free-icon/cool_4688508"},"imageURL":"/gaming/img/tiger.png","key":"ra9dev","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"gud","title":"Game Undefeatability Document (GUD)","authors":"ra9dev","tags":["gd","marketing"]},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"Am I done with the games?","permalink":"/gaming/blog/im-done"}},"content":"Ask yourself in your heart of hearts: **\u201CWHY is there a near-ZERO chance that MY GAME will FLOP?\u201D**\\n\\nAnd if the answer reveals a non-zero chance\u2026 well, you need to get GUD.\\n{/* truncate */}\\n\\n:::tip\\nVictorious warriors win first and then go to war, while defeated warriors go to war first and then seek to win.\\n\\n**Sun Tzu**\\n:::\\n\\n_The content that follows is a living example of the philosophy we preach in the studio. This document will undergo incremental improvements throughout the game development cycle._\\n\\n**Project:** Agony Dolls (WIP)\\\\\\n**Version:** 2026.05.15.A.A.A\\n\\n### Why does the game hook instantly?\\n(First 5\u201315 minutes experience)\\n\\n### Why are the characters compelling?\\n(Design, personality, progression fantasy, emotional connection)\\n\\n### Why does navigation feel fluid?\\n![ACHV_POTION_CRAFT](/img/gaming/ACHV_POTION_CRAFT.png)\\n\\nAfter fully completing PotionCraft, I fell so in love with their limited set of locations and the store navigation that I decided to just take this approach and adapt it for my game about a voodoo doll shop.\\n\\nIn short, the world of PotionCraft consists of 2D locations of different rooms, with the camera looking straight down at a 90-degree angle.\\n**To move between rooms, the player uses the WASD keys and essentially \\"flies\\" from the bedroom to the laboratory, then to the basement or behind the sales counter.**\\nThere\u2019s no default walking character like in most game engine templates \u2014 only the camera.\\n\\nAnd these are exactly the kind of design limitations that bring ergonomics to the game, significantly improving the player\u2019s quality of life.\\nThe familiar movement keybinds from larger AAA games work predictably, yet are much simpler at the same time.\\n\\n### Why is core gameplay addictive to master?\\n(Combat, building, puzzle, racing \u2014 whatever the main activity is)\\n\\n### Why is progression challenging and rewarding?\\n(Power curve, sense of growth, meaningful choices, dopamine balance)\\n\\n### Why is the world alive and worth exploring?\\n(Exploration, discovery, atmosphere, secrets, reactivity)\\n\\n### Why will players return for dozens of sessions?\\n(Long-term retention hooks, daily/weekly rewards, mastery ceiling, community)\\n\\n### Why does the game feel fair?\\n(Difficulty curve, feedback, failure recovery, anti-frustration systems)\\n\\n### Why is the experience memorable and shareable?\\n(Moments of awe, stories players will tell, social virality, uniqueness)"},{"id":"im-done","metadata":{"permalink":"/gaming/blog/im-done","source":"@site/blog/2026-02-26-im-done.md","title":"Am I done with the games?","description":"My BIG problem is that gamedev means way more to me than just a hobby, but no matter what angle I approach it from, I\u2019m extremely bad at making games \u2014 YET I CANNOT simply give up and quit.","date":"2026-02-26T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"postmortem","permalink":"/gaming/blog/tags/postmortem","description":"what went right, what went wrong, and anything learned after completing a project"}],"readingTime":1,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Tiger.Whiskers","title":"UE5 DEV + 3D ART","socials":{"steam":"https://steamcommunity.com/id/TigerWhiskers","email":"mailto:ra9dev@gmail.com","attribution":"https://www.flaticon.com/free-icon/cool_4688508"},"imageURL":"/gaming/img/tiger.png","key":"ra9dev","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"im-done","title":"Am I done with the games?","authors":"ra9dev","tags":["postmortem"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Game Undefeatability Document (GUD)","permalink":"/gaming/blog/gud"}},"content":"My BIG problem is that gamedev means way more to me than just a hobby, but no matter what angle I approach it from, I\u2019m extremely bad at making games \u2014 **YET I CANNOT simply give up and quit.**\\n\\n{/* truncate */}\\n\\nA short list of my failures:\\n\\n- 2 failed playtests on Steam\\n- 2 failed demos on Steam (hey, I actually got further than playtests!)\\n- 5 unfinished game jams on itch.io\\n- ~25 dead prototypes in UE5\\n- ~5 dead prototypes in Godot\\n\\nLike many others, I **DREAMED** of making a simple, fun little game, releasing it, and earning at least some money. But even that hope died about six months ago.\\n\\n:::danger[DUMB]\\nAnd yet here I am, literally standing on completely scorched earth, somehow still believing I can create an oasis.\\n:::\\n\\nSince it\u2019s already obvious that I\u2019ll die before I ever quit this, I\u2019ve decided to turn my entire bumpy, crater-filled journey into an online monument. Whether it ends up being a tragicomedy that warns beginners away, or a story with a happy ending \u2014 that depends only on what happens next.\\n\\nFor now, this post is just me admitting to myself: the only jam I will never skip is my own lifelong jam."}]}}')}}]);